body:
Currently, annotations associated with an instance port (or a module port) wind up stored as attributes on the declaration. This should be changed to be result attributes since ports are being represented as return values.

This aligns the representation of module/instance ports with how we represent module port annotations as argument attributes.

```scala
circuit Foo: %[[
  {"fooPort":null,"target":"~Foo|Foo>a"},
  {"barPort":null,"target":"~Foo|Foo>bar.a"}
]]
  module Bar:
    input a: UInt<1>
  module Foo:
    input a: UInt<1>

    inst bar of Bar
    bar.a <= a
```

This is currently parsed into different representations for the annotation on `Foo>a` compared to `Foo>bar.a`:
```mlir
module  {
  firrtl.circuit "Foo"  {
    firrtl.module @Bar(in %a: !firrtl.uint<1>) {
    }
    firrtl.module @Foo(in %a: !firrtl.uint<1> {firrtl.annotations = [{fooPort}]}) {
      %bar_a = firrtl.instance @Bar  {annotations = [{barPort, target = [".a"]}], name = "bar"} : !firrtl.flip<uint<1>>
      firrtl.connect %bar_a, %a : !firrtl.flip<uint<1>>, !firrtl.uint<1>
    }
  }
}
```

This should be changed to:
```mlir
%bar_a = firrtl.instance @Bar  {name = "bar"} : !firrtl.flip<uint<1>> {firrtl.annotations = [{barPort}]}
```
